<br>
Id say not worth it vs live npcs....with slay 3 and fighting undead its a different story. 3% of hits going to special translating to 20% extra damage vs undead, bout 7% extra dps per percent of specials.<br>
<br>
So, going from say 100 to 220 dex would be about a 7% dps increase if you ahd slay 3 and were fighting undead.<br>
<br>
The question then becomes how easily can you get that increase? If you have to dump too much its not worth it.....consider shaman dex potions mabye; i dont remeber offhand how much dex they give, but they would probably be worth it in this case.<br>
<br>
Mabye ill grab some potions and do at test 255 vs 223 see if it does anythign for me when doing exp. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uawlis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>awlis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 135<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/1/02 12:50:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=637.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> alot</span><hr size=1> I think it makes alot of difference.<br>
<br>
I had 112 dex before but upped this to 212 with primal weap and alot alot more crits.. with su 3 = alot more dmg.<br>
<br>
Also did a trial with a bard before primal using katta to raide dex to 255 noticable difference again.. i'd say 3% sounds right.<br>
<br>
If you killing the mobs that much faster due to increase in slays def worth a drop in ac etc. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukronadin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kronadin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blessed Protector</span><br>  Posts: 307<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/1/02 11:01:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=637.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://members.liwest.at/keiser/eqpics/song24465.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: alot</span><hr size=1> According to my experience there is a significant jump when your dex exceeds 200. <p><p align="center"><a href=
"http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=16524"><img src="http://members.liwest.at/keiser/eqpics/sig.jpg"></img></a></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urorrak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rorrak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 119<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/2/02 12:57:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=637.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: alot</span><hr size=1> I posted results of my extensive study on this topic. <br>
(You can search for it)<br>
<br>
It took around 100 dex to nearly double my crit rate. 1.72 -&gt; 3.15<br>
Moving from 175 to 212 added the most. <br>
So agrees with the 200+ theory.<br>
The study was through my CF2 stage. My rates have improved a bit with CF3<br>
<br>
On live mobs or without slay undead this is seriously not something you want to upgrade, adding a paultry 1.3% to my DPS.<br>
<br>
As Caladel points out. Slay undead makes the difference.<br>
<br>
Its been estimated that ...<br>
<br>
Slay = ((crit-bonus) x 10) + bonus.<br>
<br>
Where crit is what you would have got if it was not converted to a slay.<br>
<br>
Its been estimated .....<br>
15% of crits become slays with SU1<br>
25% of crits become slays with SU2<br>
60% of crits become slays with SU3 <br>
<br>
so ....<br>
<br>
((1.3% x 10) x 60%) = 7.8% more DPS.<br>
<br>
The potion I used on my tests was &quot;Greater potion of Accuracy&quot; +25 Dex +25 Agi -15 Sta<br>
<br>
There is another that sacrifices AGI instead of Sta but my Agi would drop below the dreaded 75 <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Two easy sources of dex are<br>
Qeynos High Tea (+5 to Dex/Agi/int/wis) (Drinks are working now)<br>
Halas meat pie (+5 Dex/Sta +30hp)<br>
